Then something's wrong with me…

Nice take on cryptozoology, but not really cutting it for me. I don't nearly dislike it enough for a downvote, but I don't like it enough to upvote it either. The part about cameras sounds somewhat like the Shy Guy to me: "Look at me, and I'll kill you".

One idea that popped into my mind, after the attack reminded me of some spell in Lovecraft's mythos (you mail-order the book from the cult of some hideous Great Old One, and get a spell, which, when performed, allows you to project yourself to any point in the world, with the caveat that anyone present will have their heads ripped off). Everyone gets eaten, except for the bonded person, and the cloud optionally chooses another bond target.

Naturally, you're under no obligation to even consider this, just thought I'd share.

Also, the alternate containment procedure is good.





